=====================================================================
SOFTWARE / CODE — Future AGPL-3.0 Release
=====================================================================

The Eidolon software, source code, cryptographic algorithms,
implementation details, parameters, test vectors, and any derivative
artifacts thereof are NOT included in this repository at this time.

When made public, the Eidolon software will be released under the
GNU Affero General Public License version 3.0 (AGPL-3.0). This
choice is intentional and reflects the project's long-term vision:

  - Anyone may use, study, modify, and redistribute the software,
    free of charge, for any purpose.
  - Modifications and derivative works must remain under AGPL-3.0,
    preserving the rights of all downstream users.
  - If the software is used to provide a network service to third
    parties, the operator must make the corresponding source code
    (including any modifications) available to those users.

This commitment is binding on Project Logos and constitutes advance
notice of the licensing terms under which the Eidolon source code
will be published. No proprietary or "all rights reserved" release
of the Eidolon code is contemplated.

Until publication, no license — express or implied — is granted to
unpublished code, algorithms, or technical specifications by this
repository. Publication occurs through the official release channel
under https://github.com/Oykdo when the project reaches its public
launch milestone.

